place.name: WALCOTT
place.gazetteerText: WALCOTT, a parish in Tunstead district, Norfolk; on the coast, 5 miles E by N of North Walsham r. station. Post town, Stalham, under Norwich. Acres, 735; of which 50 are water. Real property, £2,067. Pop., 141. Houses, 36. The property is divided among a few. The living is a p. curacy in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £43. Patron, the Bishop of N. The church is old. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
